# secrets.map — canonical mapping: sux Worker secret name -> 1Password nested ref.
# Source of truth. op migrated FLAT -> NESTED (2026-07): a value now lives at
# op://Secrets/<ITEM>/<field>, so the Worker-secret name != the op path. This file owns
# that mapping so secret-sync.sh (and humans) never guess.
#
# Format:  <WORKER_SECRET>  <TAB>  <op-ref | TIER-TAG>
# TIER-TAGS (not credentials -> NOT op-synced):
#   @switch   arming flag, set by hand out-of-git (docs/secrets.md tier 3). Never sync.
#   @setting  non-sensitive config -> belongs in wrangler.jsonc [vars], not a secret.
#   @confirm  mapping uncertain -> Colin verify before enabling sync.
#   @missing  Worker has it but op has no matching field -> re-source or drop.

